(70, 'What did my true love give to me on Christmas Eve?', 'a partridge in a pear tree | nothing | five gold rings | eleven pipers piping', 'nothing', 'Traditionally, the Twelve Days of Christmas start on December 26th (Boxing Day, St Stephen''s Day) and end on Twelfth Night/Twelfth Day (the evening of January 5th through to the end of January 6th).\r\n\r\nThe celebrations did not start until Boxing Day as Christmas Day was considered a holy day and therefore not for merrymaking, so Boxing Day is actually the first day of Christmas in the song.', 'http://www.funtrivia.com/playquiz/quiz22415719aa6a0.html', '2010-11-30 04:56:51', '2010-11-30 05:00:14'),
